 Tech Stack
•	Figma – UI/UX design and prototyping
	•	Planned Development:
	•	React Native – mobile app frontend
	•	Firebase – backend and authentication
	•	Stock Market API – real-time stock data

- Try It Out
🔗 View the interactive prototype here: [Figma Link](https://www.figma.com/proto/ekEwgB6gNlCHw7HApI9BNx/Untitled?node-id=0-1&t=JtXtr5a87sO3ywEI-1)


📚 What I Learned
	•	UI/UX Design Principles – Learned how to structure screens, design a clean interface, and create a smooth user flow for a mobile app.
	•	App Feature Planning – Practiced breaking down an app idea into functional features like portfolio tracking, stock details, and news feeds.
	•	Figma Skills – Improved proficiency in Figma, including frames, prototyping, exporting assets, and linking screens.
	•	Project Presentation – Learned how to document a project clearly on GitHub with README, screenshots, and external prototype links.
	•	Portfolio Building – Gained experience creating a professional portfolio-ready project that can be shared with recruiters.

